{"title":"New Leatt HydraDri MTB Shoes Repel Rain & Mud","link":"https://bikerumor.com/new-leatt-hydradri-mtb-shoes-repel-rain-mud/","date":1700922201000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1.jpg\" alt=\"leatt HydraDri waterproof mountain bike shoes being ridden\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Whether your wet season is actually seasonal, or it’s just a year-round thing, Leatt’s new HydraDri mountain bike shoes aim to keep your feet dry through it all.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Offered in two clipless versions, a low-top and a boot, the latter also gets a flat-pedal model. The clipless shoes use a longer-than-normal cleat channel for maximum adjustment range, and they come with spacer shims to adapt to any pedal you’re running. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both also get a 3-layer HydraDri waterproof/breathable membraneOther than that, they’re quite different…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Leatt HydraDri 5.0 Clip</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2.jpg\" alt=\"leatt HydraDri 50 waterproof mountain bike shoes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 5.0 runs <a href=\"https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=5623&amp;awinaffid=723761&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chainreactioncycles.com%2Fp%2Fleatt-hydradri-5-0-pro-clip-shoes-2024&amp;platform=pl\">$179.99</a> and uses a single dial on top of a sliding section to smoothly pull cable across a big area to secure your foot without hotspots. The upper’s outer is a mix of Dyneema for tough abrasion resistance and a knit sock-like tongue and cuff for comfort. The toe bumper is a reinforced, semi-rigid TPU for more protection.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3.jpg\" alt=\"leatt HydraDri 50 waterproof mountain bike shoes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The outsole uses their RideGrip rubber compound with a concave waffle pattern to hold onto any pins your pedals may have…or at least keep it from slipping around while you find your footing. A semi-rigid shank in the sole provides support without limiting foot feel. Available in sizes 6-13US.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Leatt HydraDri 7.0</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5.jpg\" alt=\"leatt HydraDri 70 waterproof mountain bike shoes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 7.0 <a href=\"https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=5623&amp;awinaffid=723761&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chainreactioncycles.com%2Fde%2Fp%2Fleatt-hydradri-7-0-clip-shoes-2024&amp;platform=pl\">($209.99)</a> goes harder with an integrated gaiter and water-resistant zipper. They say it’s extremely tear, puncture, and abrasion resistant.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4.jpg\" alt=\"leatt HydraDri 70 waterproof mountain bike shoes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-4-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s topped off with a button-snap elastic cuff to prevent water from dripping in from the top. Underneath is a speed lace system for quick adjustments, even with winter gloves on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6.jpg\" alt=\"leatt HydraDri 70 waterproof mountain bike shoes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Leatt-HydraDri-waterproof-mtb-shoes-6-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These have a lugged outsole with TPU-reinforced toe, heel, and perimeter and the same shank inside for foot support. Both models have an anti-compression EVA foam midsole for cushioning, and an anti-bacterial/anti-odor lining. The non-clipless model gets a black outsole and runs $199.99.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://leatt.com/us/shop/mtb/riding-apparel-mtb/shoes\" target=\"_blank\">Leatt.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-leatt-hydradri-mtb-shoes-repel-rain-mud/\">New Leatt HydraDri MTB Shoes Repel Rain &amp; Mud</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e823681b85ee5126ac8f7598962e109b45bd3284e35d72765b5111c33cb59cba","category":"Cycling"}